headlines.description: — Joel Embiid set the tone, dominating right from the start and never letting up. It was just what Philadelphia needed.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 40 points, 76ers hold off DeRozan, Bulls

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 24 points and 12 rebounds and the Minnesota Timberwolves got a big boost from their bench in a 118-105 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns scores 24 points, Timberwolves beat Pistons 118-105

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 27 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists and the Denver Nuggets beat Brooklyn 124-104 on Sunday to extend the Nets’ losing streak to eight games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has triple-double, Nuggets hand Nets 8th loss in a row

headlines.description: — Cedi Osman scored 22 points and Kevin Love had 19 as the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied from 20 down to beat Indiana 98-85 on Sunday night, shortly after agreeing to acquire shooting guard Caris LeVert from the Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers rally from 20-point deficit, beat Pacers 98-85

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 26 points and the Boston Celtics played solid defense in a 116-83 victory over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night for their season-best fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, stellar defense lead Celtics past Magic 116-83

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic went to the bench with five fouls just 53 seconds into the third quarter. Dallas' second-best point guard joined him a little bit later for the same reason.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic gets triple-double despite fouls, Mavericks top Hawks

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 33 points and tied a career high with 12 assists as the New Orleans Pelicans used a big third quarter to take control of the game and get a 120-107 win over the Houston Rockets on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram has 33 to lead Pelicans to 120-107 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — While most teams are looking ahead to next week's All-Star break, Giannis Antetokounmpo and the Milwaukee Bucks are trying to correct some bad habits they hope won't trip them up in the playoffs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 28 as Bucks past Clippers 137-113
